Yes, the operator-contact URL need only be a valid HTTP URL, but should 
contain information about the purpose of your crawl and how to contact 
you, in case anything goes wrong. Otherwise you can get a reputation as 
an irresponsible/pest crawling project (and taint Heritrix with that 
reputation as well). You might also accumulate more draconian total 
blocks from webmasters.

Regarding your BdbModule error, without more context, it&#39;s hard to tell 
what&#39;s happening.

There shouldn&#39;t be any such (java call stack) lines in the Response Code 
Report.

A problem around BdbModule.openDatabase might indicate a difficulty with 
disk operations at the &#39;state&#39; path -- if you have made any changes to 
BdbModule configuration, or are running your job on any sort of 
non-local or less-common filesystem, those would be factors to consider. 
(I don&#39;t think BDB-JE runs well over NFS, for example.)

- Gordon

